The acting was phenomenal, the effects, though minimal in most cases, were extremely well-done, and you will watch the end credits shaking in your seat. 10/10 from me. This is a good year for movies. text: This movie is riddled with issues and I am not usually the type of person that notices them? I can accept every premise about how the life form comprehends and its rate of growth? It's an unknown life and nearly anything is possible but with that said here it goes.  Why does the space station have an "Air Lock" if you can just crawl in through the engines? Any whole at all let alone one big enough for a Jack Russel to crawl into would expose you to the freezing temp and vacuum of space!  While we are at it, why would they think the thing needed oxygen to breath if it already survived in space? Didn't he lower the oxygen in the culture chamber to resemble that of early earth before it was a blue planet? He also had to raise the temp of that chamber to 20 degrees Celsius just to reanimate it.   So in short it needed warm temperatures and a low oxygen environment?   OH YEAH!!!  SPOILER ALERT  I don't think the director gave a shit about the story as long as it allowed him to do zero gravity shots!

It doesn't try to be like Alien but more over put the point out there about what we are soon likely to find in deep space. Its a great film and you have to wonder after watching it, if we are safe or whether extraterrestrial life will break through the atmosphere and kill us all. We trust in space agencies to do the right thing, yet they go about things driven by need for knowledge. Already taking diseases out into space. So they must be bringing stuff down. The movie is good and I will leave it at that.
